<item>
            <title>[LU-11891] make --mdt-index usage consistent</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11891</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10856&quot; title=&quot;running sanity now prints &amp;quot;warning: &amp;#39;-M&amp;#39; deprecated, use &amp;#39;--mdt-index&amp;#39; or &amp;#39;-m&amp;#39; instead&amp;quot; billions of times&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10856&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10856&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixed most of the cases of &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs getstripe: warning: &apos;&amp;#45;M&apos; deprecated, use &apos;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;mdt&amp;#45;index&apos; or &apos;&amp;#45;m&apos; instead&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; but missed a few in sanity test_271d, test_271e, and test_271f.  Fix those tests to use &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;mdt&amp;#45;index&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, &lt;tt&gt;lfs&lt;/tt&gt; has a few places were the usage of &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;mdt&amp;#45;index&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;mdt&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is inconsistent.  Fix those options to be consistently available across commands.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
